main event: Multiple witnesses reported seeing a bright, round, self-luminous object that maneuvered over Jamesville, New York on April 4, 1952.
interesting points: The object was described as being bluish-white in color and estimated to be 6,000 to 8,000 feet in altitude.
The object was observed making high-speed movements, including changing direction at a high rate of speed.
A second sighting of similar objects occurred about 10 minutes later, moving in a different direction at a high rate of speed.
A New York State Police officer and a deputy sheriff observed a similar object on February 23, 1952, which descended slowly and then accelerated rapidly upward.
The objects were described as being under intelligent control and making controlled, purposeful movements.
witnesses: multiple witnesses, including a New York State Police officer and a deputy sheriff
photographs: no photographs included in the report
